# Cursor AI Rules for ProfitBuild Dashboard

## Primary Reference

**All project rules, conventions, and workflows are in `CLAUDE.md` at the project root.**

Read `CLAUDE.md` before making any changes. It is the single source of truth for:
- Database migration workflow (critical — mismatches cause deployment failures)
- Edge function deployment and version pinning
- Code conventions and architectural rules
- Feature flags and known gotchas
- Outstanding audit items and tech debt

## Cursor-Specific Notes

### Pre-deployment Checklist

Before deploying any edge function, run `ReadLints` on the file to catch syntax errors. This supplements the general pre-deploy checks documented in `CLAUDE.md`.

### MCP Tool Names

When using Supabase MCP in Cursor, the tool names are:
- `mcp_supabase_apply_migration` — DDL operations (CREATE, ALTER, DROP)
- `mcp_supabase_execute_sql` — queries and DML (SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE)
- `mcp_supabase_deploy_edge_function` — deploy edge functions
- `mcp_supabase_list_edge_functions` / `mcp_supabase_get_edge_function` — verify deployments

For the 4 branded-email functions (`send-auth-email`, `send-receipt-notification`, `send-training-notification`, `generate-media-report`), always include `_shared/brandedTemplate.ts` in the `files` array. See `CLAUDE.md` for full deployment details and pinned versions.

